# SvelteKit Conventions

## Svelte 5

This project uses Svelte 5 with runes mode enabled.

- Use `$state()`, `$derived()`, `$effect()` — not legacy reactive declarations
- Use `$props()` for component props — not `export let`
- Use snippet syntax for slot-like patterns
- Prefer `{#snippet}` over `<slot>`

## SvelteKit patterns

- Server-side data loading uses `+page.server.ts` and `+layout.server.ts`
- Route groups use the `(group)` directory convention (e.g. `(app)`)
- Prefer server-side loading over client-side fetching for initial data
- Use `$env/dynamic/private` for server-only environment variables

## File organization

```
src/
  routes/         → pages and layouts
  lib/
    components/   → reusable UI components ($components)
    layouts/      → layout primitives ($layouts)
    styles/       → global styles ($styles)
    util/         → utilities ($util)
    config/       → app configuration ($config)
    server/       → server-only code
```

## Testing

- Unit tests: Vitest with browser mode (`.spec.ts`)
- E2E tests: Playwright
- Configs live in `.config/` directory
